 <h4>
  WSU Sustainable Ag prof Featured in National Geographic
 </h4>
 <p>
  <em>
   National Geographic
  </em>
  asks, Will “Food of the Future to Be More Diverse?” In answering that question,
  <em>
   National Geo
  </em>
  talked to WSU professor Steve Jones, an expert in sustainable agricultural. “From the perspective of the plate, the foods we’ll eat in the future will likely look and taste a lot like what we eat today. But take a closer peek, and tomorrow’s dinner becomes very different indeed.”
  <a href="http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2009/06/090609-future-food-sustainable.html">
   Read more in National Geographic »
  </a>
